function clean_column(col::AbstractString)
    return replace(strip(lowercase(col)), r"[ -]" => "_")
end
```

This function takes a string `col` as input, lowercases it, strips any leading or trailing whitespaces, and then replaces all spaces and hyphens with an underscore. The `replace` function is used with a regular expression `r"[ -]"` to match all spaces and hyphens, and the replacement string `"_"` is passed as the second argument. The `strip` function is used to remove leading and trailing whitespaces, and the `lowercase` function is used to convert all characters to lowercase. The resulting cleaned column name is returned as the output.
